  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca-\u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca-\u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1-\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4-\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7-20\u0dad\u0dca-30\u0dad\u0dca-\u0d85\u0dad\u0dbb-\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2-\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf/11-394869",
  "time_ut": 1656311382,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dbd\u0dca \u0dc5\u0db8\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dad\u0dd4 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0da7 20\u0dad\u0dca 30\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0dad\u0dbb \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "School fares will be increased by 20 to 30 percent",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Ruwan Prazad, President of the All Ceylon Inter-Provincial School Transport Association, said at a meeting held at the Ambalangoda headquarters today (27) that he would have to increase the transport fare by 20 to 30 percent in line with the increase in fuel prices and that the increase would definitely be announced on the 1st of July. Said at a press conference.",
        "Mr. Prasad said that his association was also considering increasing the fares of the Private Passenger Transport Bus Association.",
        "Mr. Prasad said that his association will also increase the fares of private passenger buses from July 1, in line with the increase in bus fares.",
        "Raising fuel prices is not our problem .It's not just a national disaster like Corona .It's the fault of the rulers who rule the country alone .We are not prepared to pay for this .But this is not the case for school children and their parents.",
        "The child who went to Montessori then has to go to Montessori for two years instead of one year .What a heinous crime .How unfortunate the country is .We are doing this job now thinking about this situation .Our industry is in a state of unspeakable collapse. Break it down completely .If it goes like this, it will happen in the future.",
        "We have to run every day when rural schools are started. Even if one child goes to school, we have to give our services. It's failing .We have children going to school too .What can we do about it? Parents can not even imagine how to send their children to school.",
        "We do not want to increase transportation costs .We want to maintain our industry .This industry can not do it for profit now .We also know that we have to increase transportation rates as soon as fuel prices increase .We increase tariffs without thinking about the increase in spare parts prices. If we think about it we have to increase transport fares by about 100 percent.",
        "Ruwan Preethi Kumara, Chief Organizer of the All Ceylon Inter-Provincial School Children's Transport Association also spoke on the increase in fares."
      ],
